<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-04-02T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-04-02T17:00:00-05:00" n="921" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d921">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">390D.11/189: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-04-02T17:00:00-05:00">April
                                        2, 1940—5 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>23. Your 21, February 29, 11 a.m. and Department’s 12, February 29,
                                11 a.m.<note n="58" xml:id="d921fn58">Latter not printed.</note> The
                                Department is willing to transmit to Turkey requests of American
                                citizens that they be released from Turkish allegiance, and will
                                require satisfactory evidence that the persons whose requests are
                                transmitted have acquired American citizenship.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>